Report_Definition_English: Recruitment (hiring) is a core function of human resource management. Recruitment refers to the overall process of attracting; selecting and appointing suitable candidates for jobs (either permanent or temporary) within an organization. Recruitment can also refer to processes involved in choosing individuals for unpaid positions; such as voluntary roles or unpaid trainee roles. Managers; human resource generalists and recruitment specialists may be tasked with carrying out recruitment; but in some cases public-sector employment agencies; commercial recruitment agencies; or specialist search consultancies are used to undertake parts of the process. Internet-based technologies to support all aspects of recruitment have become widespread.
